{
  "name": "ToolEQA on HM-EQA",
  "description": "ToolEQA (Zhai et al., arXiv 2510.20310, ICLR 2026 in review) — tool-augmented active explorer for HM-EQA, monolith-first port. Each iter is one ReAct step inside tooleqa__step (backend env, transformers.agents): build prompt from the Thought/Code/Observation scratchpad, call Qwen2.5-VL with the current rgb, parse code, exec via evaluate_python_code with 6 tools (VisualQA / ObjectLocation2D / ObjectLocation3D / ObjectCrop / GoNextPointTool / final_answer; SegmentInstance dead upstream). VQA→Qwen, locate_2d/3d→env_detany3d, GoNextPointTool→tooleqa_explore__go_next (full Explore-EQA TSDF frontier step + teleport, which itself steps env_hmeqa over HTTP — so env_hmeqa__step is NOT a canvas loop node). Depth rides the ANY wire (lossless metric depth; DEPTH normalizes to [0,1]). PortBench v1 target (zero-shot vs paper Table 5: 62.3% SR / 18.26m).",
